        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 4:24AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 424 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles west of Mandaree, or 14 miles east of Watford City, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mandaree and Johnsons Corner.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
